    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Welcome to Music Lab!\r\n\r\nThis is a lab that lets you combine **coding** and **music**! This level is all about exploration! Try clicking things! Try dragging things! Explore this space! \r\n\r\nSee how many of these you can do:\r\n\r\n- Drag out a block\r\n- Connect two blocks\r\n- Play a track\r\n- Change the track\r\n- Play 3 tracks in a row: <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-drum\" style=\"color: #E565F5;\"></i> &nbsp; Beat </span>, <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9;\"></i> &nbsp; Bass </span>, then <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px;  white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-guitars\" style=\"color: #64D25A;\"></i> &nbsp; Lead </span> tracks\r\n- Change the order of your tracks\r\n- Change where the song starts playing in the timeline\r\n- Delete a block\r\n- Clear the workspace and start over\r\n- Play 3 tracks simultaneously\r\n\r\n",
